Revision history for RPi-StepperMotor

3.1802 UNREL
    - Fixed speed(): its validation used an inverted grep (`$speed ne $_`) that
      could never be false, so the croak was dead code and any value was
      accepted; it now croaks on anything other than 'full' or 'half'
    - Added t/05-unit.t: HW-free coverage of the step patterns and counter wrap
      (cw/ccw, full/half) via an injected mock expander, the _turns() gearing
      math, and the new()/pins/speed/direction validation croaks
    - Removed the duplicate 3D-printing STLs from docs/steppermotor_framework/;
      they are kept once, with the RPi::WiringPi test-platform structure in the
      rpi-wiringpi repo, and the POD now points there
    - Added off(), which de-energizes the motor (drives all coil pins LOW) while
      leaving them as OUTPUT so the motor stays usable; cleanup() now calls it,
      so it also de-energizes expander-driven motors, which it previously left
      energized

3.1801    2026-06-12
        - Bump prereq of WiringPi::API to 3.1803
        - Bump prereq of RPi::Const to 1.05

2.3605  2019-06-19
        - added new examples (multi-motor and fork)
        - added new name() feature so each motor object can have its own name
          (closes #1)
        - added ability to use an MCP23017 GPIO Expander to drive the motor
        - added blurb about how to identify clockwise operation from counter
          clockwise (closes #2)

2.3604  2018-03-14
        - Pi day!
        - added Fritzing breadboard layout/docs directory
        - added cleanup() to clean up pins after use

2.3603  2018-03-13
        - remove code that unsets the pins. This is the user's or
          RPi::WiringPi's responsibility
        - added new "stepper" binary, updated POD

2.3602  2018-03-13
        - fix unformatted SYNOPSIS

2.3601  2018-03-13
        First version, released on an unsuspecting world.

